Class DialogDeleteConfirmFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • DialogFragment

        • com.chdryra.android.mygenerallibrary.DialogAlert
          • com.chdryra.android.mygenerallibrary.DialogDeleteConfirmFragment 

  • public class DialogDeleteConfirmFragment
extends DialogAlert
    A standardised delete confirmation alert dialog. Asks the user to confirm with a "Yes" or "Cancel".

    There is a static method showDeleteConfirmDialog(.) that can be called to show the default confirmation dialog. This is preferable to constructing the dialog yourself.

      • showDeleteConfirmDialog

        public static void showDeleteConfirmDialog(java.lang.String deleteWhat,
                           Fragment targetFragment,
                           int requestCode,
                           FragmentManager fragmentManager)
        Shows a standard delete confirm dialog. This should be used rather than the constructor.
        Parameters:
        deleteWhat: - Title of dialog will be "Delete (deleteWhat)?"
        targetFragment: - The fragment that will receive the answer.
        requestCode: - The requestCode that the fragment issued and listens for on the callback.
        fragmentManager: - The fragment manager that handles the showing of the dialog.
